column10: from Boerboom: "Based on the age it best fits with the Bradbury Creek granodiorite, which makes sense looking at S-22"

from Boerboom: "That rock has a strong metamorphic foliation and what I described as ragged hornblende of metamorphic origin, so most likely pre-ECMB.  It was cut by some undeformed granite dikelets.  That is from within the Becker embayment.  There is a drill core nearby (EC-15  1786 ± 43 Ma) that is not deformed"
